1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,503
[Teresa] <i>I've watched</i>
<i>Maya Mae Kalaw's documentary.</i>

2
00:00:03,586 --> 00:00:05,005
<i>I just found out that</i>
<i>Datu Rahman has surrendered.</i>

3
00:00:05,088 --> 00:00:07,340
[Marcus] <i>Espina brought him</i>
<i>to the headquarters.</i>

4
00:00:07,424 --> 00:00:08,508
<i>Datu Rahman turned himself in to him.</i>

5
00:00:09,092 --> 00:00:11,052
- To Allan?
- You call him by his first name?

6
00:00:11,136 --> 00:00:12,429
[Marcus] <i>Are you close with him?</i>

7
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:15,849
[Teresa] <i>When you went to the island,</i>
<i>I took Allan home with me.</i>

8
00:00:15,932 --> 00:00:17,600
Remember that show-off rookie cop

9
00:00:17,684 --> 00:00:19,894
at the office that I told you about?

10
00:00:19,978 --> 00:00:21,438
<i>That's him. Allan.</i>

11
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:25,108
Maybe you haven't really
gotten to know him yet.

12
00:00:25,191 --> 00:00:29,112
[Dionisio] <i>General Villanueva believes</i>
<i>that Datu Rahman is telling the truth,</i>

13
00:00:29,195 --> 00:00:31,990
<i>that the syndicate's protector</i>
<i>is from NLEA.</i>

14
00:00:32,073 --> 00:00:33,116
PREVIOUSLY

15
00:00:33,199 --> 00:00:34,325
What are we going to do, General?

16
00:00:34,409 --> 00:00:38,371
We're going to give them what they need.

17
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:42,417
[Manuel] <i>We'll give them someone</i>
<i>who can take the fall.</i>

18
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:46,629
The accusations against
Datu Rahman are not true.

19
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:51,509
[Azuelo] <i>Agent Reyes went back</i>
<i>to Damai Island to get evidence.</i>

20
00:00:51,593 --> 00:00:55,346
These are the photos of the firearms
that Datu Rahman's group got from the sea.

21
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:56,639
[Lara] <i>It's confirmed.</i>

22
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:59,559
Marcus was up to something.
You know what to do.

23
00:00:59,642 --> 00:01:01,019
[in English] Understood, madam.

24
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:03,313
[boy] <i>Jalil!</i>

25
00:01:03,396 --> 00:01:04,773
[Aminah] <i>Jalil!</i>

26
00:01:04,856 --> 00:01:07,484
[Aminah, in Arabic]
<i>Praise be to God! You're finally here!</i>

27
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:10,153
[Aminah] <i>Armed men are attacking</i>

28
00:01:10,236 --> 00:01:13,073
<i>our neighboring islands.</i>

29
00:01:13,156 --> 00:01:14,866
[Aminah] They rob people,

30
00:01:14,949 --> 00:01:18,244
and the women are being sold off.

31
00:01:18,328 --> 00:01:22,290
[man] All the illegal weapons
Datu Rahman used to seize

32
00:01:22,874 --> 00:01:24,751
are everywhere now.

33
00:01:24,834 --> 00:01:26,795
[Felix] <i>Head to Damai Island.</i>

34
00:01:26,878 --> 00:01:31,299
Get all the weapons Datu Rahman hid there.

35
00:01:31,382 --> 00:01:35,303
After that, kill
every single person left there.

36
00:01:35,386 --> 00:01:36,888
I'll send my men over now.

37
00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:42,060
[Felix] <i>This is my revenge</i>
<i>on you, Jalil Abubakar.</i>

38
00:01:46,731 --> 00:01:52,904
[mysterious theme music playing]

39
00:01:59,410 --> 00:02:02,539
BLOOD VS DUTY

40
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:06,376
[somber music playing]

41
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:22,475
- [dog barks]
- [Lilian] Sir Marcus.

42
00:02:23,101 --> 00:02:24,477
- Have a cup of coffee.
- [Marcus] Oh…

43
00:02:25,645 --> 00:02:27,105
You'll have to forgive me.

44
00:02:27,188 --> 00:02:29,816
I don't have anyone I can ask
to buy the fancy stuff.

45
00:02:29,899 --> 00:02:30,984
Thanks, anyway.

46
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:32,443
You shouldn't have bothered.

47
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:34,237
Oh, I would've done more.

48
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:35,989
If I had known you were coming,

49
00:02:36,072 --> 00:02:37,782
I would've cooked for you.

50
00:02:38,616 --> 00:02:39,534
Thank you.

51
00:02:39,617 --> 00:02:41,536
It's no big deal.

52
00:02:41,619 --> 00:02:43,037
Grandma,

53
00:02:43,121 --> 00:02:44,998
how's life here?

54
00:02:45,081 --> 00:02:46,207
- [gentle music playing]
- [Lilian scoffs]

55
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:47,917
Aren't you finding it hard to live alone?

56
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:49,377
I'm used to it.

57
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:52,755
I just keep myself busy by…

58
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:54,257
taking care of the plants.

59
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:56,092
Did you see them?

60
00:02:56,175 --> 00:02:59,012
- They're pretty, right? So many flowers.
- [chuckles] Yes.

61
00:02:59,095 --> 00:03:00,305
[Marcus chuckles softly]

62
00:03:01,431 --> 00:03:03,516
Uh, Sir Marcus…

63
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:06,603
I saw Datu Rahman's video.

64
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:08,563
[rooster crowing]

65
00:03:08,646 --> 00:03:11,900
Was he telling the truth when he said…

66
00:03:12,692 --> 00:03:15,111
that someone inside the NLEA is…

67
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:16,905
Yes, Grandma.

68
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:22,076
I believe him.

69
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:26,080
That's what I think, too.

70
00:03:27,457 --> 00:03:28,499
[sniffles]

71
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:31,878
- [cries, sniffles]
- [sighs deeply]

72
00:03:31,961 --> 00:03:33,671
[Lilian] Heartless people…

73
00:03:34,172 --> 00:03:39,135
[sniffles] My grandson died
while performing his duties.

74
00:03:42,138 --> 00:03:45,141
And he died at the hands
of those he thought were his allies.

75
00:03:45,725 --> 00:03:47,018
[cries]

76
00:03:48,102 --> 00:03:50,021
- [softly] Grandma…
- [sniffles]

77
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:54,317
I came here for a reason.

78
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:57,487
I have something to tell you.

79
00:03:58,655 --> 00:04:01,074
Something you need to know.

80
00:04:01,157 --> 00:04:02,575
Harold…

81
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:05,536
He's alive.

82
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:08,081
[rooster crowing]

83
00:04:08,164 --> 00:04:09,874
He's currently on the island.

84
00:04:28,643 --> 00:04:30,353
[pensive music playing]

85
00:04:30,436 --> 00:04:31,771
Where's Marcus?

86
00:04:32,563 --> 00:04:33,856
Who knows?

87
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:35,483
And Espina?

88
00:04:36,317 --> 00:04:37,151
Beats me.

89
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:40,321
He probably just went out.

90
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:42,323
Why?

91
00:04:43,032 --> 00:04:44,367
[in English] They're up to something.

92
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:50,915
[hopeful music playing]

93
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:52,583
Harold is alive?

94
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:55,211
[crying, sniffles]

95
00:04:56,087 --> 00:04:57,880
How's he doing over there?

96
00:04:57,964 --> 00:04:59,674
Is he safe?

97
00:04:59,757 --> 00:05:02,677
Is he eating well?

98
00:05:03,636 --> 00:05:05,888
- Harold is doing fine.
- [sniffles]

99
00:05:07,098 --> 00:05:11,769
[inhales] He helped a boy on the night
of the encounter on the island.

100
00:05:11,853 --> 00:05:16,691
That boy's family is taking care of him
to show their gratitude.

101
00:05:18,359 --> 00:05:20,945
Don't worry, Grandma,
you won't have to wait long.

102
00:05:21,029 --> 00:05:23,364
- You'll be reunited with him soon.
- [sniffles]

103
00:05:24,574 --> 00:05:25,825
Just have a little patience.

104
00:05:25,908 --> 00:05:28,077
You'll see him once this is all over.

105
00:05:28,953 --> 00:05:30,079
For now,

106
00:05:30,747 --> 00:05:34,042
Harold is safer there than here.

107
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:37,295
[cries softly, breathes deeply]

108
00:05:37,378 --> 00:05:39,505
I understand. [sniffles]

109
00:05:39,589 --> 00:05:40,757
Thank you.

110
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:44,719
[breathing shakily] But Sir Marcus…

111
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,513
Promise me that

112
00:05:48,514 --> 00:05:51,559
you will find whoever
did this to my grandchild.

113
00:05:52,602 --> 00:05:54,896
They shouldn't be able
to hurt anyone else.

114
00:05:54,979 --> 00:05:58,149
Nobody should grieve again
because of their greed.

115
00:05:59,984 --> 00:06:03,196
- [sobbing]
- Grandma…

116
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:07,116
Grandma.

117
00:06:08,868 --> 00:06:11,287
I promise you that I won't stop

118
00:06:11,370 --> 00:06:14,791
until they get justice
for what happened to them.

119
00:06:14,874 --> 00:06:17,251
[gentle music playing]

120
00:06:17,335 --> 00:06:19,045
- I swear that to you.
- [sniffles]

121
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:21,464
Thank you.

122
00:06:21,547 --> 00:06:22,799
‪-[rooster crowing]
‪-[softly] Thank you.

123
00:06:23,966 --> 00:06:24,801
‪[sniffles]

124
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:34,644
[music intensifies]

125
00:06:41,859 --> 00:06:44,904
[melancholic music playing]

126
00:06:56,374 --> 00:06:59,794
- [Jalil]
- Son, we need to protect our people!

127
00:06:59,877 --> 00:07:03,089
- [man] We need to go!
- [Jalil] No, stop!

128
00:07:03,172 --> 00:07:04,924
[grim music playing]

129
00:07:07,301 --> 00:07:09,262
[people screaming]

130
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:11,139
[Jalil] <i>Run! Run away!</i>

131
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:13,224
- [gunshots blasting]
- [indistinct]

132
00:07:13,307 --> 00:07:15,852
[indistinct]

133
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:18,104
‪[ethereal music playing]

134
00:07:18,187 --> 00:07:19,272
HUSIN PARILA

135
00:07:19,355 --> 00:07:20,189
‪[gunshots blasting]

136
00:07:23,359 --> 00:07:26,446
- [gunshots]
- [people screaming, groaning]

137
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:44,088
[Jalil] <i>I didn't want any of you</i>

138
00:07:44,589 --> 00:07:46,966
<i>to get hurt or to die.</i>

139
00:07:48,551 --> 00:07:50,803
<i>I just wanted to resolve the problem</i>

140
00:07:50,887 --> 00:07:53,681
<i>without having to resort to violence</i>

141
00:07:53,764 --> 00:07:55,683
<i>and having blood spilled.</i>

142
00:07:57,477 --> 00:08:01,189
<i>Because I want to believe</i>
<i>in a peaceful world,</i>

143
00:08:02,648 --> 00:08:06,277
<i>where no one needs to get hurt and die.</i>

144
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:09,947
[tense music playing]

145
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:11,449
[man] Stop resisting!

146
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:12,992
There's nothing you can do anyway.

147
00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:14,619
There are only two of you.

148
00:08:14,702 --> 00:08:16,704
[young Jalil] Father, stop! Let's just go!

149
00:08:16,787 --> 00:08:18,372
- [man] I'm not scared of you!
- [young Jalil] Stop, please!

150
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:20,249
- You'd have to go through me
- [young Jalil cries]

151
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:22,126
before you get your way on our island!

152
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:24,879
[suspenseful music playing]

153
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:29,175
[man] This one's brave, huh?
Should we just kill him?

154
00:08:30,968 --> 00:08:32,803
We were minding our own business
here on the island.

155
00:08:33,971 --> 00:08:35,556
We don't want any trouble.

156
00:08:37,016 --> 00:08:38,309
But if you insist on doing what you want,

157
00:08:38,976 --> 00:08:41,062
- we won't hesitate to fight.
- [gun cocks]

158
00:08:42,146 --> 00:08:45,107
[dramatic sting]

159
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:50,279
‪[dramatic sting]

160
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:12,176
- Boss!
- Let's go.

161
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:13,427
- Let's retreat!
- There's a lot of them!

162
00:09:14,428 --> 00:09:15,263
[man] Move!

163
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:31,112
We should've finished them off.

164
00:09:31,195 --> 00:09:32,071
[young Jalil] Father!

165
00:09:32,154 --> 00:09:35,658
[panting]

166
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:38,911
You never change, Sali.

167
00:09:39,745 --> 00:09:41,289
There's a time to fight

168
00:09:41,372 --> 00:09:43,332
and a time for diplomacy.

169
00:09:45,835 --> 00:09:47,044
Don't you like that?

170
00:09:47,878 --> 00:09:49,880
We drove them away without bloodshed

171
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:51,090
or anyone getting hurt.

172
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:56,053
[foreboding ethereal music playing]

173
00:10:16,324 --> 00:10:17,700
[Jalil] <i>But I was wrong.</i>

174
00:10:18,659 --> 00:10:22,288
<i>Maybe if I hadn't stopped them</i>
<i>from using weapons,</i>

175
00:10:22,371 --> 00:10:23,831
<i>more of you would still be alive.</i>

176
00:10:24,957 --> 00:10:26,792
<i>Maybe it wouldn't have come to this.</i>

177
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:29,670
<i>Forgive me.</i>

178
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:32,048
[in Arabic] <i>I swear by Allah.</i>

179
00:10:33,257 --> 00:10:38,262
<i>I won't stop until whoever</i>
<i>did this to you pays for it.</i>

180
00:10:38,346 --> 00:10:40,514
<i>I promise.</i>

181
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:44,226
[screaming]

182
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:50,941
[breathing heavily]

183
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:55,363
[dramatic music playing]

184
00:11:00,034 --> 00:11:00,868
‪[music intensifies]

185
00:11:03,704 --> 00:11:09,043
[morose music playing]

186
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:09,854
[young Jalil] <i>Father?</i>

187
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:12,481
<i>Father?</i>

188
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:15,651
Father?

189
00:12:17,445 --> 00:12:18,612
Father!

190
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:20,364
Father!

191
00:12:21,532 --> 00:12:22,908
Father!

192
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:24,785
Father!

193
00:12:25,369 --> 00:12:26,454
Father!

194
00:12:26,996 --> 00:12:29,415
Where are you, Father?!

195
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:34,545
[crying]

196
00:12:34,628 --> 00:12:37,381
Father!

197
00:12:38,924 --> 00:12:41,844
Father…

198
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:42,887
[Datu Rahman] Jalil!

199
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:45,222
Jalil!

200
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:47,057
Father!

201
00:12:48,642 --> 00:12:50,519
- [Datu Rahman] Where are you?
- I'm here, Father!

202
00:12:50,603 --> 00:12:51,437
[Datu Rahman] Jalil!

203
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:55,232
[panting]

204
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:56,400
Jalil!

205
00:12:56,484 --> 00:12:58,110
[panting]

206
00:12:58,694 --> 00:13:01,697
[panting] Jalil, where did you go?

207
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:05,409
I thought something happened to you…
Wait, are you hurt?

208
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:08,662
- Are you hurt?
- No.

209
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:11,999
I thought something terrible
happened to you.

210
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:14,710
- [softly] Jalil.
- [whimpers]

211
00:13:14,793 --> 00:13:17,171
[Jalil] <i>Even though</i>
<i>we weren't blood-related,</i>

212
00:13:18,005 --> 00:13:21,342
<i>you never made me feel</i>
<i>like I was an outsider.</i>

213
00:13:21,425 --> 00:13:23,677
<i>You treated me like family.</i>

214
00:13:24,261 --> 00:13:25,513
<i>When I disappeared,</i>

215
00:13:25,596 --> 00:13:29,808
<i>you never stopped, Father,</i>
<i>until you found me.</i>

216
00:13:30,392 --> 00:13:31,852
<i>That's why I won't stop either.</i>

217
00:13:31,936 --> 00:13:35,814
<i>I won't stop until I find you.</i>

218
00:13:36,315 --> 00:13:39,401
[morose music playing]

219
00:14:05,844 --> 00:14:07,930
[young Jamilah, in Tausug] Help! Help!

220
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:09,431
- Jamilah?
- [young Jamilah] Jalil!

221
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:10,516
- [young Jalil] Where are you?
- [young Jamilah] Help!

222
00:14:10,599 --> 00:14:12,810
Jamilah, what are you doing up there?!

223
00:14:12,893 --> 00:14:15,229
I was trying to pick some fruit,

224
00:14:15,312 --> 00:14:17,648
but now I can't get down!

225
00:14:17,731 --> 00:14:19,483
Jamilah, you're so stubborn.

226
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:23,320
- Just wait!
- [young Jamilah] Jalil, hurry!

227
00:14:23,404 --> 00:14:25,865
[young Jalil] Just wait, Jamilah.
Your brother's here.

228
00:14:26,448 --> 00:14:27,449
- Hang on.
- [young Jamilah panting]

229
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:29,076
- Hold on, okay?
- [young Jamilah crying]

230
00:14:29,159 --> 00:14:31,662
I'm here now. Are you okay?

231
00:14:31,745 --> 00:14:32,913
I'm here.

232
00:14:32,997 --> 00:14:34,123
- Come on.
- [screams]

233
00:14:34,206 --> 00:14:35,666
- [grunts]
- [whimpers]

234
00:14:37,626 --> 00:14:39,962
- [groans] Are you okay?
- [crying]

235
00:14:40,045 --> 00:14:41,964
- [crying]
- Are you okay?

236
00:14:42,047 --> 00:14:43,716
[groans]

237
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:46,051
Jalil, what's wrong?

238
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:47,428
[groans]

239
00:14:47,511 --> 00:14:49,179
It's nothing.

240
00:14:49,263 --> 00:14:50,639
- I'm okay. I'm fine.
- Jalil!

241
00:14:51,557 --> 00:14:53,225
- [young Jamilah crying]
- [young Jalil] <i>Are you okay?</i>

242
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:55,561
[morose music continues]

243
00:15:13,329 --> 00:15:16,040
[in Tausug] Oh no, Jalil. I'm so sorry.

244
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:19,835
Ouch, Jamilah!

245
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:22,004
- That hurts. Wait, please.
- [young Jamilah grunts]

246
00:15:22,087 --> 00:15:23,464
Come on, Jalil!

247
00:15:23,547 --> 00:15:29,178
You were so brave
shielding me when I fell,

248
00:15:29,261 --> 00:15:32,473
but now you keep saying "ouch"
while getting treated!

249
00:15:32,556 --> 00:15:35,601
I got hurt because of your stubbornness!

250
00:15:35,684 --> 00:15:37,061
I'm really sorry.

251
00:15:37,144 --> 00:15:39,480
And don't worry, Jalil.

252
00:15:39,563 --> 00:15:41,941
When I grow up, I'm going to be a nurse.

253
00:15:42,024 --> 00:15:45,527
So someone can take care of you
every time you get hurt.

254
00:15:45,611 --> 00:15:48,906
Is that really why you want
to become a nurse?

255
00:15:48,989 --> 00:15:51,742
- [both giggle]
- Fine.

256
00:15:51,825 --> 00:15:56,330
I want to take care of Father
and everyone in our village too.

257
00:15:56,413 --> 00:16:00,167
- Of course, especially you!
- Ouch, Jamilah!

258
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:01,585
- Just treat me later.
- [giggles]

259
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:03,796
Look at it. It's huge.

260
00:16:05,297 --> 00:16:07,716
Jalil, just because someone's
taking care of you now

261
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:10,719
doesn't mean you can stop being careful.

262
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:11,804
[young Jalil snickers]

263
00:16:11,887 --> 00:16:13,097
[mocking]

264
00:16:14,723 --> 00:16:16,183
Ouch, Jamilah!

265
00:16:16,266 --> 00:16:18,310
- That hurt.
- [young Jamilah] Really?

266
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:22,398
This will teach Jalil to be more careful.

267
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:24,066
[chuckles]

268
00:16:24,149 --> 00:16:26,860
But you're the reason I got hurt!

269
00:16:26,944 --> 00:16:29,238
- [young Jamilah giggles]
- You two are so silly.

270
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:32,741
- Aren't you?
- It's her fault! Look at me.

271
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:36,203
- Finish cleaning his wound.
- No! Ouch, Jamilah! [laughs]

272
00:16:36,286 --> 00:16:37,246
Enough!

273
00:16:37,329 --> 00:16:38,706
- You're so naughty!
- It might get infected.

274
00:16:38,789 --> 00:16:40,582
- Let Jamilah finish.
- No! Aah!

275
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:42,501
- There you go.
- Ouch!

276
00:16:42,584 --> 00:16:44,628
- [young Jalil laughing]
- [young Jamilah giggling]

277
00:16:44,712 --> 00:16:45,838
[young Jalil] Jamilah…

278
00:16:45,921 --> 00:16:47,381
[young Jalil] <i>Ah!</i>

279
00:16:50,259 --> 00:16:53,679
[morose music playing]

280
00:16:59,059 --> 00:17:00,769
You're sad again.

281
00:17:02,896 --> 00:17:04,106
[sighs]

282
00:17:04,982 --> 00:17:07,484
It's been a month since Mother died.

283
00:17:07,568 --> 00:17:10,988
Every day…

284
00:17:11,905 --> 00:17:14,033
I miss her more.

285
00:17:15,659 --> 00:17:18,203
What about you, Jalil?

286
00:17:18,954 --> 00:17:20,664
Do you miss her?

287
00:17:22,624 --> 00:17:24,001
[sighs sharply]

288
00:17:24,793 --> 00:17:25,961
Jamilah…

289
00:17:26,587 --> 00:17:27,796
Of course, I miss her.

290
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:29,006
I loved her.

291
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:30,549
She took care of me.

292
00:17:30,632 --> 00:17:32,843
She raised me as her own.

293
00:17:32,926 --> 00:17:35,220
She was like a mother to me.

294
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:38,015
What about your real mother?

295
00:17:39,558 --> 00:17:41,018
Do you miss her?

296
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:45,355
No.

297
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:49,902
She doesn't really cross my mind.

298
00:17:52,196 --> 00:17:53,447
But…

299
00:17:54,239 --> 00:17:57,034
Sometimes I wonder, Jamilah.

300
00:17:57,785 --> 00:18:00,829
I wonder if they miss me.

301
00:18:01,371 --> 00:18:04,416
[morose music continues]

302
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:07,669
Brother.

303
00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:12,132
Mother is gone.

304
00:18:13,801 --> 00:18:17,888
It's just you, me, and Father from now on.

305
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:20,641
We have to stick together.

306
00:18:21,850 --> 00:18:23,644
Promise me that.

307
00:18:23,727 --> 00:18:27,314
‪[chuckles] No matter what happens,
‪we stay together.

308
00:18:27,898 --> 00:18:29,608
And I will always protect you.

309
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:31,610
I promise.

310
00:18:34,696 --> 00:18:36,115
Oh, Jamilah.

311
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:39,368
[young Jalil sighs softly]

312
00:18:43,664 --> 00:18:44,581
Father.

313
00:18:47,376 --> 00:18:51,213
- [ethereal music playing]
- [Datu Rahman sighs]

314
00:18:51,296 --> 00:18:55,801
My children, we're in this together.

315
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:57,761
- Hmm?
- We're in this together.

316
00:18:57,845 --> 00:19:00,180
[chuckling]

317
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:04,685
[gushing, giggling]

318
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:09,731
[pensive music playing]

319
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:14,570
[doorbell buzzing]

320
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:19,116
[intriguing music playing]

321
00:19:38,302 --> 00:19:39,678
Gabriel Lozano?

322
00:19:40,262 --> 00:19:41,388
That's me.

323
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:51,648
[dramatic sting]

324
00:19:54,276 --> 00:19:55,319
T-Thanks…

325
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:04,703
[unsettling music playing]

326
00:20:52,167 --> 00:20:53,794
[Gabriel] <i>I've received the package.</i>

327
00:20:53,877 --> 00:20:55,462
<i>Thanks for the discount.</i>

328
00:20:56,755 --> 00:20:58,090
NO PROBLEM. I'M ON YOUR SIDE

329
00:20:58,173 --> 00:20:59,549
NO ONE WILL EVER BULLY YOU AGAIN

330
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:03,804
[unsettling music continues]

331
00:21:11,895 --> 00:21:14,022
[music turns tense]

332
00:21:38,588 --> 00:21:41,842
NEXT ON BLOOD VS DUTY

333
00:21:41,925 --> 00:21:44,845
[man] <i>We Tausugs don't start trouble,</i>

334
00:21:44,928 --> 00:21:48,390
<i>but we never back down from a fight.</i>

335
00:21:48,473 --> 00:21:52,894
[Jalil] I will teach you
how to shoot a gun properly.

336
00:21:52,978 --> 00:21:56,064
[Jalil] <i>Pointing a gun at someone</i>
<i>means you're ready to kill.</i>

337
00:21:56,148 --> 00:21:58,984
[Azuelo] If I know something is not right,

338
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:01,611
I don’t deserve the title of General.

339
00:22:01,695 --> 00:22:06,074
Think long and hard
about what you're doing!

340
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:10,370
Didn't I tell you
not to show your face here?

341
00:22:10,454 --> 00:22:11,580
Back off!

342
00:22:11,663 --> 00:22:12,831
[boy] <i>You think a gun will scare us?</i>

343
00:22:12,914 --> 00:22:14,041
[gun fires]

344
00:22:14,124 --> 00:22:16,209
[screaming]

345
00:22:16,293 --> 00:22:18,962
There's an active shooter at a school.
East Valley Montessori.

346
00:22:19,546 --> 00:22:23,675
[Azuelo] <i>If we fail this mission,</i>
<i>many children will die!</i>

347
00:22:24,176 --> 00:22:27,179
Dad, please remember, I love you and Mom.

348
00:22:27,262 --> 00:22:30,098
If you go in like this,
you'll only put your son at more risk.

349
00:22:31,099 --> 00:22:32,517
[Gabriel] <i>You ruined my life!</i>

350
00:22:32,601 --> 00:22:34,352
[Marcus] Our overall goal for this mission

351
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:36,480
<i>is to have zero casualties. Understood?</i>

352
00:22:36,563 --> 00:22:37,522
- [gunshots]
- [screams]

353
00:22:37,606 --> 00:22:42,611
At last, our plans are in motion, Dante.

354
00:22:42,694 --> 00:22:46,782
BLOOD VS DUTY
